      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Add needed sandbox activation mode",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a first-class `agents.defaults.sandbox.mode = \"needed\"` option for chat-first deployments where sandbox backends such as Docker may be temporarily unavailable.\n\nIn `needed` mode, ordinary embedded-agent turns do not preflight or create a sandbox runtime. Sandbox-bound exec activation still resolves `host=auto` to the sandbox, lazily creates the configured backend on first exec, and fails closed if that backend is unavailable instead of falling back to gateway/node host execution.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Extend sandbox config schema/types with `needed`.\n- Add run-vs-tool sandbox activation semantics.\n- Wire embedded exec tools with a cached lazy sandbox resolver.\n- Keep exec fail-closed when lazy sandbox resolution returns no runtime.\n- Update `sandbox explain`, doctor/audit guidance, and sandbox docs.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/sandbox/tool-policy.test.ts src/agents/sandbox.resolveSandboxContext.test.ts src/agents/exec-defaults.test.ts src/agents/bash-tools.exec.path.test.ts src/commands/sandbox-explain.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/bash-command.stop.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:src`\n- `pnpm lint:core`\n- `pnpm lint:docs`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nFixes #80296",
        "branch": "codex/80296-sandbox-needed-mode",
